1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,074


2
00:01:52,034 --> 00:01:54,161
You better get married soon.

3
00:01:54,870 --> 00:01:57,831
You're starting to look old.

4
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,544
My dad has been saying that to me
since I was 15...

5
00:02:02,669 --> 00:02:06,131
because nice Greek girls are supposed
to do three things in life.

6
00:02:06,215 --> 00:02:10,219
Marry Greek boys, make Greek babies,
and feed everyone...

7
00:02:10,594 --> 00:02:12,429
until the day we die.

8
00:03:04,439 --> 00:03:07,442
When I was growing up,
I knew I was different.

9
00:03:08,110 --> 00:03:10,821
The other girls were blond and delicate.

10
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:14,408
And I was a swarthy 6-year-old
with sideburns.

11
00:03:14,491 --> 00:03:17,077
I so badly wanted to be
like the popular girls...

12
00:03:17,244 --> 00:03:19,371
all sitting together, talking...

13
00:03:19,705 --> 00:03:22,291
eating their Wonder Bread sandwiches.

14
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:24,084
What's that?

15
00:03:24,585 --> 00:03:26,128
It's moussaka.

16
00:03:26,628 --> 00:03:28,130
Moose ka-ka?

17
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:32,885
And while the pretty girls
got to go to Brownies...

18
00:03:32,968 --> 00:03:35,053
I had to go to Greek school.

19
00:03:44,605 --> 00:03:47,441
At Greek school,
I learned valuable lessons like.

20
00:03:47,524 --> 00:03:51,570
"If Nick has one goat and Maria has nine,
how soon will they marry?"

21
00:03:55,741 --> 00:03:59,870
My mom was always cooking foods
filled with warmth and wisdom...

22
00:03:59,912 --> 00:04:03,290
and never forgetting that side dish
of steaming-hot guilt.

23
00:04:03,332 --> 00:04:06,293
Niko, don't play with the food.

24
00:04:06,502 --> 00:04:09,338
When I was your age, we didn't have food.

25
00:04:09,463 --> 00:04:10,881
-Ma?
-What?

26
00:04:11,340 --> 00:04:13,842
Why do I have to go to Greek school?

27
00:04:14,009 --> 00:04:18,597
When you get married, don't you want to be
able to write your mother-in-law a letter?

28
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,932
Niko, come on, eat!

29
00:04:21,141 --> 00:04:25,854
We lived in a normal, middle-class Chicago
neighborhood of tasteful, modest homes.

30
00:04:25,979 --> 00:04:29,358
Our house, however,
was modeled after the Parthenon...

31
00:04:29,441 --> 00:04:33,654
complete with Corinthian columns,
and guarded by statues of the gods.

32
00:04:34,154 --> 00:04:37,658
In case the neighbors had
any doubts about our heritage...

33
00:04:37,699 --> 00:04:41,328
they could just check out
our subtle tribute to the Greek flag.

34
00:04:41,787 --> 00:04:44,331
My dad believed in only two things...

35
00:04:44,331 --> 00:04:47,709
that Greeks should educate non-Greeks
about being Greek...

36
00:04:47,835 --> 00:04:52,714
and that any ailment, from psoriasis
to poison ivy, could be cured with Windex.

37
00:04:55,092 --> 00:04:59,388
Six years later, I was 12.
Athena, my older, perfect sister, was 15.

38
00:04:59,429 --> 00:05:01,640
And my brother, Nick, was 11.

39
00:05:01,682 --> 00:05:05,811
Every morning, my dad would lecture us
on the "history of our people...

40
00:05:05,853 --> 00:05:08,772
"the great civilization, the Greeks. "

41
00:05:09,398 --> 00:05:12,985
Now, name three things the Greeks did first.

42
00:05:14,695 --> 00:05:17,322
Astronomy, philosophy, and democracy.

43
00:05:17,614 --> 00:05:19,241
Bravo! Very good.

44
00:05:20,909 --> 00:05:22,661
Now, give me a word...

45
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,329
any word...

46
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:28,208
and I show you, how the root of that word...

47
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,334
is Greek.

48
00:05:29,418 --> 00:05:31,044
Sweet Lord, again.

49
00:05:32,087 --> 00:05:35,048
How about "arachnophobia"?

50
00:05:35,799 --> 00:05:39,678
"Arachna," that comes from
the Greek word for spider...

51
00:05:40,262 --> 00:05:43,557
and "phobia" is a phobia, it means "fear."

52
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:46,852
So, "fear of spiders." There you go.

53
00:05:47,895 --> 00:05:51,190
Okay, Mr. Portokalos,
how about the word "kimono"?

54
00:05:52,149 --> 00:05:53,859
-"Kimono."
-Good one.

55
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,778
Kimono, kimono.

56
00:05:58,071 --> 00:06:01,950
Of course, "kimono"
comes from the Greek word...

57
00:06:02,284 --> 00:06:05,370
"cheimonas," which means "winter."

58
00:06:05,829 --> 00:06:09,124
So, what do you wear in the wintertime...

59
00:06:09,249 --> 00:06:11,502
to stay warm? A robe.

60
00:06:11,919 --> 00:06:15,130
You see, "robe," "kimono." There you go.

61
00:06:22,137 --> 00:06:24,848
-Bye-bye.
-Goodbye, Mr. Portokalos.

62
00:06:29,978 --> 00:06:30,938
Toula!

63
00:06:33,941 --> 00:06:35,901
You should be proud to be Greek.

64
00:06:40,989 --> 00:06:42,574
A couple more years went by...

65
00:06:42,658 --> 00:06:45,744
and my dad brought his mother
from Greece to live with us...

66
00:06:45,827 --> 00:06:48,121
because we weren't weird enough.

67
00:07:04,179 --> 00:07:05,681
-Where is she going?
-Mama, please!

68
00:07:05,764 --> 00:07:07,975
The Greeks and the Turks friends now.

69
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:10,018
We told my grandma the war was over...

70
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:12,688
but she still slept
with a knife under her pillow.

71
00:07:15,649 --> 00:07:17,234
Stop hitting me!

72
00:07:18,652 --> 00:07:21,947
Niko, be careful.
She has a very mean punch.

73
00:07:34,710 --> 00:07:39,173
Nice Greek girls who don't find a husband
work in the family restaurant.

74
00:07:39,214 --> 00:07:42,759
So, here I am, day after day, year after year.

75
00:07:43,010 --> 00:07:45,762
Thirty, and way past my expiration date.

76
00:07:46,013 --> 00:07:48,140
My God. It's freezing.

77
00:07:49,641 --> 00:07:54,021
Fotoula! You closed last night,
you're opening this morning?

78
00:07:54,271 --> 00:07:55,522
I have no life.

79
00:07:57,191 --> 00:07:59,610
Fotoula, you talk to me sometime.

80
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:02,362
Ma, you're gonna make me
swallow my tongue.

81
00:08:03,780 --> 00:08:06,283
Toula! Is Nikki here?

82
00:08:08,202 --> 00:08:09,161
What's up?

83
00:08:09,244 --> 00:08:12,414
No, my Nikki. She was supposed
to come over to curl my hairs.

84
00:08:12,539 --> 00:08:15,709
Nick, did you check the meat
before you signed for it?

85
00:08:15,834 --> 00:08:18,170
-Dad checked it.
-It better be fresh.

86
00:08:18,378 --> 00:08:22,090
My brother has two jobs,
to cook and to marry a Greek virgin.

87
00:08:22,174 --> 00:08:25,469
Voula, have something to eat
before you go to work.

88
00:08:26,303 --> 00:08:30,390
If nagging was an Olympic sport,
my Aunt Voula would have a gold medal.

89
00:08:30,474 --> 00:08:32,935
Taki, you couldn't wait for me?

90
00:08:34,061 --> 00:08:35,187
Sorry.

91
00:08:35,354 --> 00:08:37,689
Sorry, sorry. Don't "sorry" me.

92
00:08:39,107 --> 00:08:42,444
Look at this. Rash.
Somebody gave me the mati.

93
00:08:42,569 --> 00:08:45,280
-Put some Windex on it.
-Oh, Gus, please.

94
00:08:46,073 --> 00:08:48,200
Voula! This works.

95
00:08:48,659 --> 00:08:51,870
Last night, my toe was as big as my face.

96
00:08:54,414 --> 00:08:56,542
Why you not wait for me?

97
00:08:57,584 --> 00:09:00,254
Gus. He wants to talk.

98
00:09:03,882 --> 00:09:06,385
Anyway, I tell her...

99
00:09:06,969 --> 00:09:11,390
-I will send her to Greece to find somebody.
-She's not too old.

100
00:09:17,813 --> 00:09:19,273
She's okay.

101
00:09:19,439 --> 00:09:20,774
In Greece...

102
00:09:21,149 --> 00:09:22,943
don't tell anyone how old she is.

103
00:09:23,318 --> 00:09:25,988
-She won't go.
-She won't go?

104
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:29,491
It's like she don't want to get married.

105
00:09:32,119 --> 00:09:34,121
Come on, boys. Go in there.

106
00:09:34,329 --> 00:09:38,000
My sister married young and became
a Greek baby-breeding machine.

107
00:09:42,171 --> 00:09:44,047
Hey, guys. Come on, get out.

108
00:09:44,131 --> 00:09:45,299
Just a quick coffee.

109
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:48,844
I have to drop the boys off at hockey
and then I got to get to the Jewel.

110
00:09:48,969 --> 00:09:51,430
-Bread?
-Pantyhose are on for 99 cents.

111
00:09:51,471 --> 00:09:55,267
Then the priest is coming to bless
the new house, so I have to make diples.

112
00:09:55,350 --> 00:09:58,478
Can you believe it? I'm out of honey.
Put that back for me.

113
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,022
You dropped my tzatziki.

114
00:10:00,147 --> 00:10:01,523
-Angelo!
-Nikki, shut up.

115
00:10:01,648 --> 00:10:04,234
My cousins have two volumes,
loud and louder.

116
00:10:04,359 --> 00:10:06,320
...your big-ass girlfriend. Thanks, Toula.

117
00:10:06,403 --> 00:10:07,321
Hey, Toula.

118
00:10:07,362 --> 00:10:08,614
We're not that late.

119
00:10:09,281 --> 00:10:10,407
Hi, everybody.

120
00:10:11,992 --> 00:10:15,120
Nikki, how come you didn't come
to curl my hair this morning?

121
00:10:15,204 --> 00:10:17,498
Ma, I had to drop Dimo at work.

122
00:10:17,789 --> 00:10:21,460
Now I got to go open the travel agency,
because some jack-off...

123
00:10:21,502 --> 00:10:23,504
and his big-ass girlfriend are too busy.

124
00:10:23,629 --> 00:10:28,008
Tell her I open up the cleaners every day.
It's time she does something for a change.

125
00:10:28,050 --> 00:10:29,801
You know who's there this morning?

126
00:10:29,885 --> 00:10:32,387
-You're always at the beauty parlor.
-My husband.

127
00:10:32,471 --> 00:10:35,307
-Your nails, hair, everything.
-Don't talk about my hair.

128
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:38,143
You're lazy.
You and your big-ass girlfriend do nothing.

129
00:10:38,185 --> 00:10:40,812
Did somebody sit on your hair?
It looks a little flat.

130
00:10:40,854 --> 00:10:42,814
Angelo, bite me.

131
00:10:42,940 --> 00:10:44,775
Disgusting, be a lady.

132
00:10:45,234 --> 00:10:46,318
Ma.

133
00:10:46,860 --> 00:10:48,153
Angelo.

134
00:10:48,737 --> 00:10:51,073
Ande. Come on, boys. Let's go.

135
00:10:51,823 --> 00:10:54,701
-Athena, when did you come?
-Hi, Ma. Bye, Ma.

136
00:10:54,743 --> 00:10:55,869
You're going?

137
00:10:55,911 --> 00:10:58,539
I'm going to the Jewel.
I'll get you some pantyhose.

138
00:10:58,580 --> 00:11:01,458
No queen size. They make me look fat.

139
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,710
No more fun and games.

140
00:11:04,002 --> 00:11:05,587
I didn't do it!

141
00:11:07,172 --> 00:11:08,632
Who put the menus there?

142
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:14,304
Toula, what's this?

143
00:11:15,889 --> 00:11:17,641
Toula, what is this?

144
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:19,893
-I don't know.
-Mama.

145
00:11:22,563 --> 00:11:24,481
Now don't forget, I need the plates and--

146
00:11:24,565 --> 00:11:27,901
And the pizza for the buffet.
You told me at dinner. Go. My God.

147
00:11:29,778 --> 00:11:31,530
All right, we're gonna go.

148
00:11:32,531 --> 00:11:35,033
-I wanna drive.
-You're driving me crazy, let's go.

149
00:11:36,618 --> 00:11:38,453
Just watch. Don't run.

150
00:11:45,878 --> 00:11:49,298
-To me, she looks okay.
-Okay? What okay? Nokay.

151
00:11:49,339 --> 00:11:53,260
She's not okay. Look.
Athena is married with three children.

152
00:11:53,343 --> 00:11:55,971
And I'll get married, Pops, I promise.

153
00:11:58,348 --> 00:12:01,101
You have plenty of time, Niko.

154
00:12:01,810 --> 00:12:05,564
And you'll always have Toula
to run the restaurant.

155
00:12:06,273 --> 00:12:09,151
It's true. Toula will never leave you.

156
00:12:58,492 --> 00:13:00,494
I wish I had a different life.

157
00:13:01,245 --> 00:13:03,997
I wish I was braver and prettier...

158
00:13:04,373 --> 00:13:05,999
or just happy.

159
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:10,921
But it's useless to dream,
because nothing ever changes.

160
00:13:28,230 --> 00:13:31,024
-Hey, what's going on?
-Hi. How are you?

161
00:13:31,441 --> 00:13:33,360
-Good. You?
-Oh, good.

162
00:13:34,903 --> 00:13:37,489
-Cool place.
-Yeah, it's adorable.

163
00:13:39,408 --> 00:13:42,244
You missed a hell of a party the other night.

164
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:44,830
Look at that.

165
00:13:45,330 --> 00:13:47,583
That could have been you
with that arm around her.

166
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,460
You set me up with her already.

167
00:13:52,838 --> 00:13:54,798
-Nancy?
-Hanson's picnic.

168
00:13:56,758 --> 00:13:59,553
No, that was Pamela. This is Nancy.

169
00:14:03,348 --> 00:14:05,058
They look the same.

170
00:14:07,352 --> 00:14:08,770
Well, maybe.

171
00:14:09,188 --> 00:14:10,814
So, you want me to set you up?

172
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:13,609
They're all the same, Mike.

173
00:14:26,038 --> 00:14:27,372
-Hi.
-Hi.

174
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:33,295
Sorry, my brain stopped.

175
00:14:33,629 --> 00:14:37,841
You ever have one of those days,
when it's going along and then stops?

176
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:41,762
Here I am, standing here,
your own private Greek statue.

177
00:14:46,934 --> 00:14:49,853
-Could I get some more coffee, please?
-Sure.

178
00:14:51,730 --> 00:14:53,023
Thank you.

179
00:15:03,784 --> 00:15:05,577
All right, let's go.

180
00:15:05,828 --> 00:15:08,413
-What do you mean? I just got here.
-I got a class.

181
00:15:08,539 --> 00:15:10,958
I love the spice on these potatoes.
What is that?

182
00:15:10,999 --> 00:15:12,793
Like I care. Come on.

183
00:15:12,918 --> 00:15:16,380
Giving a pop quiz,
and I can't wait to hear the groans.

184
00:15:17,673 --> 00:15:18,841
Man, you're tough.

185
00:15:18,924 --> 00:15:21,760
I'm giving a test on Hamlet,
but I give fair warning.

186
00:15:33,021 --> 00:15:34,147
Hi.

187
00:15:35,732 --> 00:15:37,150
Keep the change.

188
00:15:51,623 --> 00:15:54,084
You like this, Pops? For the new menu?

189
00:15:54,918 --> 00:15:58,213
-Where did you get that?
-I drew it, Dad.

190
00:16:20,777 --> 00:16:23,322
Dad, I've been going through
our inventory...

191
00:16:23,447 --> 00:16:27,409
and I've noticed that we've been doing
a lot of unnecessary ordering.

192
00:16:27,451 --> 00:16:30,871
I've been thinking that
maybe we should update our system.

193
00:16:31,288 --> 00:16:33,540
We could get a computer.

194
00:16:34,625 --> 00:16:38,045
I don't know if you remember,
but I got all A's in Computers.

195
00:16:38,128 --> 00:16:41,173
But there's a lot of new stuff to learn now...

196
00:16:41,590 --> 00:16:45,719
so, if you want, I could go to college
and take a few courses.

197
00:16:49,723 --> 00:16:50,849
Why?

198
00:16:52,559 --> 00:16:55,229
Why you want to leave me?

199
00:16:55,270 --> 00:16:56,980
I'm not leaving you.

200
00:16:57,022 --> 00:16:59,191
Don't you want me
to do something with my life?

201
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:02,694
Yes! Get married! Make babies!

202
00:17:03,737 --> 00:17:05,614
You look so old!

203
00:17:23,340 --> 00:17:26,218
Hey, Toula. Come on.

204
00:17:27,344 --> 00:17:29,179
I know what you want.

205
00:17:30,097 --> 00:17:33,100
You have, how you say, a spirit.

206
00:17:34,351 --> 00:17:37,521
You want to see things. You want to learn.

207
00:17:38,564 --> 00:17:40,691
I know, you're from my side.

208
00:17:43,068 --> 00:17:46,405
Come on. Don't you worry.
I'm gonna talk to him.

209
00:17:47,489 --> 00:17:50,200
Dad is so stubborn. What he says goes.

210
00:17:50,284 --> 00:17:52,161
"The man is the head of the house."

211
00:17:52,452 --> 00:17:54,663
Let me tell you something, Toula.

212
00:17:54,788 --> 00:17:58,750
The man is the head,
but the woman is the neck.

213
00:17:59,001 --> 00:18:02,504
And she can turn the head
any way she wants.

214
00:18:05,424 --> 00:18:07,009
My baby.

215
00:18:07,551 --> 00:18:09,970
Don't cry. Come on.

216
00:18:10,721 --> 00:18:13,932
And what is wrong with Toula
going to school downtown?

217
00:18:14,057 --> 00:18:15,767
They use drugs downtown.

218
00:18:15,851 --> 00:18:19,688
What are you saying? Are you saying
that Toula will get involved with drugs?

219
00:18:19,730 --> 00:18:22,649
No, but somebody will say to her:

220
00:18:23,108 --> 00:18:26,778
"Take this bag down to the bus depot,"
and she'll do it.

221
00:18:27,154 --> 00:18:29,531
She's not stupid. She's smart.

222
00:18:30,032 --> 00:18:33,494
I know she's smart,
so what for she needs more school?

223
00:18:33,577 --> 00:18:35,829
She's smart enough for a girl.

224
00:18:36,788 --> 00:18:39,124
You think you're smarter than me?

225
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:41,919
No, I mean, you know--

226
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:43,879
What? What do you mean?

227
00:18:44,004 --> 00:18:47,591
I run the restaurant, I cook, I clean...

228
00:18:47,841 --> 00:18:51,011
I wash for you, and I raised three kids...

229
00:18:51,428 --> 00:18:53,639
and I teach Sunday school.

230
00:18:54,097 --> 00:18:58,143
You know, it's lucky for me
I have you to tie my shoes.

231
00:19:00,270 --> 00:19:01,939
Maria....

232
00:20:20,100 --> 00:20:22,769
-Is this seat taken?
-Sure.

233
00:20:27,274 --> 00:20:28,400
Hi.

234
00:21:04,561 --> 00:21:06,980
That's what I want to talk to you about.

235
00:21:10,651 --> 00:21:13,070
-Look at you. What are you talking about?
-What?

236
00:21:13,362 --> 00:21:15,572
I don't like my butt. Taki likes it.

237
00:21:16,615 --> 00:21:20,410
I won't pretend the travel industry
is something I've always wanted to do.

238
00:21:20,452 --> 00:21:24,331
I'm not gonna pretend that,
but I'm saying that it's different.

239
00:21:24,331 --> 00:21:26,500
You know I've been learning
about computers?

240
00:21:26,542 --> 00:21:28,502
There's this course, a seminar.

241
00:21:28,544 --> 00:21:30,671
It's all about computers and tourism.

242
00:21:30,671 --> 00:21:33,090
There are all the latest applications
and programs.

243
00:21:33,131 --> 00:21:36,844
I could apply it here, Thia.
And your business would double or triple.

244
00:21:36,969 --> 00:21:39,721
You could be with Thio more,
and you could take a vacation.

