in the Greek Orthodox Church.

574
00:51:04,194 --> 00:51:06,530
Nikki's going to be your godmother.

575
00:51:10,617 --> 00:51:11,535
You know...

576
00:51:12,452 --> 00:51:14,288
the word "baptism"...

577
00:51:15,330 --> 00:51:18,834
comes from the Greek word "baftisia. "

578
00:51:19,001 --> 00:51:20,794
That's where we dip the baby...

579
00:51:20,919 --> 00:51:24,131
in a beautiful, little silver basin.

580
00:52:00,167 --> 00:52:01,919
It's not so bad?

581
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:05,380
Are you kidding? Any minute now,
he's going to look at me and go:

582
00:52:05,422 --> 00:52:07,674
"Right, you're so not worth this."

583
00:52:09,593 --> 00:52:10,802
Yes, you are.

584
00:52:29,780 --> 00:52:31,031
You're all oily.

585
00:52:32,783 --> 00:52:34,117
I'm Greek, now.

586
00:52:35,994 --> 00:52:37,454
Thank you so much.

587
00:52:49,550 --> 00:52:52,845
So, for "Happy Easter,"
we say "Khristos Anesti."

588
00:52:52,970 --> 00:52:55,389
Then the other person says back,
"Alithos Anesti."

589
00:52:55,430 --> 00:52:59,560
So if you want to say "Happy Easter,"
you go, "Khristos Anesti." So try it.

590
00:53:02,062 --> 00:53:03,021
That's good.

591
00:53:07,442 --> 00:53:08,443
Hey, Dad.

592
00:53:13,657 --> 00:53:16,118
Mr. Portokalos, Khristos Anesti.

593
00:53:24,001 --> 00:53:25,502
-He likes you.
-Yes?

594
00:53:26,128 --> 00:53:28,130
I told you to watch the boys.

595
00:53:28,213 --> 00:53:30,799
They'll be fine with the video games.

596
00:53:30,841 --> 00:53:34,261
-You turn their brains to mush.
-I can't do anything right.

597
00:53:34,720 --> 00:53:38,223
Ian, if you're going to be in this family,
I'll get you some earplugs...

598
00:53:38,348 --> 00:53:41,894
because the Portokalos women,
if they're not nagging somebody, they die!

599
00:53:42,769 --> 00:53:46,690
-You're in trouble when I tell my sister.
-Tell me what?

600
00:53:50,194 --> 00:53:51,820
Where is he?

601
00:53:52,738 --> 00:53:54,948
Khristos Anesti.

602
00:53:56,950 --> 00:53:59,119
Alithos Anesti, Thia.

603
00:53:59,369 --> 00:54:01,163
Toula, you're engaged!

604
00:54:01,580 --> 00:54:04,124
We never think it would happen for you.
Never.

605
00:54:05,542 --> 00:54:08,629
-Taki, didn't we say that?
-We never think this day will come.

606
00:54:09,171 --> 00:54:11,798
-And it came!
-Is this him?

607
00:54:12,549 --> 00:54:14,384
Yes, sorry. Everyone, this is Ian.

608
00:54:14,510 --> 00:54:16,428
Ian!

609
00:54:53,799 --> 00:54:55,050
Hello, Ian.

610
00:55:14,194 --> 00:55:15,988
I want to see the rock.

611
00:55:20,701 --> 00:55:21,994
-Hey, Ian.
-Hey.

612
00:55:22,119 --> 00:55:24,079
-You like that dance?
-Yeah.

613
00:55:24,121 --> 00:55:26,790
Okay, Jennie has something
she wants to ask you.

614
00:55:26,874 --> 00:55:28,333
-No, she doesn't.
-Go on.

615
00:55:28,500 --> 00:55:29,710
Jennie, just ask me.

616
00:55:29,918 --> 00:55:31,420
Does he have any brothers?

617
00:55:31,879 --> 00:55:33,672
No, he's an only child.

618
00:55:33,797 --> 00:55:37,009
I've got to tell you,
I've never seen my sister so happy.

619
00:55:38,552 --> 00:55:41,680
If you hurt her, I'll kill you
and make it look like an accident.

620
00:55:43,140 --> 00:55:46,393
Jesus, look at your face. It's just a joke.

621
00:55:46,810 --> 00:55:47,769
Good one.

622
00:55:47,978 --> 00:55:50,814
No, the good one is, "I've got a gun."
Yeah, I've got a gun...

623
00:55:50,939 --> 00:55:52,774
and I swear, I'll jam it up your....

624
00:55:52,900 --> 00:55:54,568
Ian, I got you again!

625
00:55:55,569 --> 00:55:58,280
-Here, eat some rice.
-I don't want any rice, I'm good.

626
00:55:58,447 --> 00:56:00,824
No, "I'm good."
I could snap you like a chicken!

627
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:03,368
Come on, lighten up.

628
00:56:03,619 --> 00:56:06,580
I'll lighten you when I take out your kidneys.

629
00:56:08,499 --> 00:56:09,958
One more time, Ian.

630
00:56:10,250 --> 00:56:13,504
-Hey, Angelo.
-Hey, Ian, we're going to kill you!

631
00:56:41,323 --> 00:56:43,075
Ian, Aunt Voula.

632
00:56:43,700 --> 00:56:45,118
Let me touch your hair.

633
00:56:49,832 --> 00:56:52,000
-Okay, Thia Voula?
-No.

634
00:56:52,084 --> 00:56:53,252
-Thia Voula?
-Yes?

635
00:56:55,462 --> 00:56:58,090
When you come to my house
and I cook for you?

636
00:56:58,173 --> 00:57:00,592
-Okay.
-Thia, that might be a problem.

637
00:57:00,717 --> 00:57:03,178
Problem? I'm the best cook
in the family. Tell him.

638
00:57:03,220 --> 00:57:05,097
-I did, didn't l?
-Twice.

639
00:57:05,180 --> 00:57:06,390
Okay, then.

640
00:57:07,891 --> 00:57:09,309
It's just....

