645
00:57:19,153 --> 00:57:20,612
No, he doesn't eat meat.

646
00:57:20,654 --> 00:57:22,990
What do you mean, "He don't eat no meat"?

647
00:57:26,743 --> 00:57:29,371
That's okay, I'll make lamb.

648
00:57:29,580 --> 00:57:30,664
Come.

649
00:57:31,290 --> 00:57:33,000
Come and dance.

650
00:58:06,408 --> 00:58:07,367
Silence.

651
00:58:10,621 --> 00:58:11,872
It's delicious.

652
00:58:14,541 --> 00:58:18,170
We took a look at my calendar,
our calendar...

653
00:58:18,754 --> 00:58:21,757
to set a day for the big day...

654
00:58:21,798 --> 00:58:25,010
sometime at the end of October,
mid-November?

655
00:58:25,052 --> 00:58:27,763
-Sometime in there, yeah.
-Wonderful.

656
00:58:27,888 --> 00:58:30,349
I'll call the Club and see what's open.

657
00:58:30,891 --> 00:58:32,017
The Club?

658
00:58:32,351 --> 00:58:35,229
The North Shore Country Club,
for the wedding, of course.

659
00:58:36,188 --> 00:58:38,690
We're going to get married
in Toula's church...

660
00:58:38,774 --> 00:58:41,568
because we're not very religious,
and her family is.

661
00:58:41,819 --> 00:58:44,321
Really is. Show them the brochure.

662
00:58:45,113 --> 00:58:46,615
Oh, that. Yeah.

663
00:58:50,410 --> 00:58:53,622
My cousin Nikki made me this.

664
00:58:53,747 --> 00:58:56,542
She tends to save things.
This is from her prom.

665
00:58:57,084 --> 00:58:58,877
She makes lamps and....

